<TITLE> Policeman hurt in bomb attack on police checkpoint </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 25 (bdnews24.com)  A police constable and a pedestrian were injured when two small bombs were hurled at a police check post in Malibagh in the city Wednesday evening. Police constable Ali Hasain was admitted to Rajarbagh Police Hospital. Khilgaon police sub-inspector Abdul Motaleb Bhuiyan told bdnews24.com that police were searching vehicles setting up a check post in front of Abul Hotel in Malibagh Chowdhurypara. At about 7:15pm, some unidentified youths in a taxicab hurled two crackers at the check post and sped away . The pedestrian could not be immediately identified. Police were looking for the motive behind the attack. bdnews
